member.example:
The default virtual keyboard of the VirtualKeyboard control is defined in the following way:

AddKey("q");
AddKey("w");
AddKey("e");
// ...
AddKey("p");
AddKey("Backspace");

AddLine(); // Starts a new row of keys.
AddSpace(4); // Creates a larger space at the beginning of the second row.

AddKey("a");
AddKey("s");
// ...
